@BOOK{Burr2003-eh,
  title     = "Social Constructionism",
  author    = "Burr, Vivien",
  abstract  = "This accessible, yet scholarly, textbook aims to introduce
               students to the area of social science theory and research that
               has come to be known as social constructionism. Using a variety
               of examples from everyday experience and from existing research
               in areas such as personality, sexuality and health, the basic
               theoretical assumptions of social constructionism are clearly
               explained. Key debates, such as the nature and status of
               knowledge, truth, reality and the self are given in-depth
               analysis in an accessible style. The theoretical and practical
               issues relevant to social constructionist research are
               illustrated with examples from real empirical studies, and the
               different approaches to social constructionist research are
               clearly defined. While the text is broadly sympathetic to social
               constructionism, the weaknesses of the approach are also
               addressed through a critical approach to the material, and in
               the final chapter the theory is subjected to a more extensive
               critique. Social Constructionism, Second Edition, extends and
